  1. Emotion (visual - based) metrics can single out successful videos for social media. For example, video results that signify a smile is present through a good part of the video might fair better than videos where a dour attitude is present. Positive attitudes provide compelling viewing, because facial expressions matter when presenting!
  2.  Also, there should be a happy medium between too little being said and "information overload" in an ideal video so that it's watchable for the average viewer interested in business intelligence topics. Such a metric could be the Rate of Words Being Said or Total Words being Said in the video.
